{
  "texts": [
    "Hierarchical architecture: Dong and Zhang (2016) proposed hierarchical holistic scoring architecture for prompt-specific and cross-prompt AES.",
    "Their approach introduced wordlevel and sentence-level convolutional layers, leading to domain adaptation and a significant performance improvement compared to previous models in this category.",
    "Two-stage hybrid neural network: Jin et al. (2018) proposed a two-stage neural network approach, prompt independent stage and prompt-dependent stage.",
    "In the first stage (promptindependent stage), the focus is on selecting representative positive and negative sample data.",
    "The selection process of the samples depend on handcrafted features such as word length, number of prepositions, and number of unique words."
  ]
}